# Branch & PR Workflow

## Branches

Never push to `main` directly. Create a feature branch first:

```bash
git checkout -b feat/short-description   # new feature
git checkout -b fix/short-description    # bug fix
git checkout -b chore/short-description  # tooling / config
git checkout -b refactor/scope-name      # no behavior change
git checkout -b docs/scope-name          # docs / rules / comments
```

## Pull requests

After pushing, **enable auto-merge with squash** rather than blocking:

```bash
git push -u origin HEAD
gh pr create --title "..." --body "$(cat <<'EOF' ... EOF)"
gh pr merge <n> --auto --squash
```

PR body should have `## Summary`, `## Test plan`. Use a HEREDOC so the
shell doesn't eat backticks. Include before/after metrics when fixing
performance, Sonar, or test coverage.

## CI

Required checks (set in branch protection on `main`):
- **Backend** — `ruff check` + `ruff format --check` + `ty check` + `pytest -q`
- **Frontend (jest)** — `jest` against `static/js/*.js`

Both must be green for auto-merge to fire. If a Dependabot PR sits red
because `main` moved, comment `@dependabot rebase` on it.

## Verifying state

Before declaring "merged":

```bash
gh pr view <n> --json mergeable,mergeStateStatus,autoMergeRequest
```

Look for `state: CLEAN` and `mergeable: MERGEABLE`. After merge,
prune local branches: `git fetch --prune && git branch -d <name>`.
